//display inline - block -Z 
block: (div)
- start a new line and take all horizantal width
- width: take the width of the parent 
- height: take the height of the content
- you can alter with and the height

inline:  (span)
- does not start new line
- take the width and height of its content 
- you can not alter height and width 
- margin top and bottom does not affected 

inline block: 
- take it's width of it's content 
- you can alter width, height, margin-top and margin bottom

ref:
https://medium.com/@DaphneWatson/css-display-properties-block-inline-and-inline-block-how-to-tell-the-difference-7d3a1e6e3051


Dispaly flex: 
Flexbox, or CSS3 Flexible Box, is a super lightweight way to lay out UI components on a web page.
- main axis, corss axis
- flex-direction
- justify-content
- align-item 


ref: 
https://medium.com/@emmabostian/css3-flexbox-the-cool-kid-on-the-block-cca8141cbee9



